A vintage 1980s-style illustration of a massive, intricate mechanical calculator made of brass gears, copper pipes, and analog dials, sitting atop a towering stack of yellowed paper documents and punch cards. The machine has multiple spinning wheels showing numbers and mathematical symbols, with steam wisping from small vents. In the background, an old wooden office desk with scattered blueprints and a slide rule. The color palette features warm sepia tones, aged cream paper textures, and burnished metallic bronze. The scene is lit by warm afternoon sunlight streaming through a dusty window, casting long shadows across the cluttered workspace. The overall mood conveys the weight and complexity of measuring and calculating large-scale technical investments.
